                <summary>Last Friday, William Robinson, a black man, attempted to rob the store of
                    Hugh Glenn and Co. Two African American men, John J. Christian and Alex Nellons,
                    heard the noise and attempted to stop him. A scuffle ensued in which Christian
                    was struck on the head with a piece of iron. The thief took refuge in a house in
                    Gallowstown where police arrested him after Christian and Nellons stood watch.
                    Robinson was brought before Mayor Allen who committed him to jail until the
                    grand jury could hear his case.</summary>
                <note/>
